<div id="post-1523030" class="blog-post position-4 even-post"><div class="even-post-inner blog-post-inner"><h1 class="title"><a href="http://softwarelivre.org/terceiro/blog/debian-ruby-sprint-2016-day-1">Debian Ruby Sprint 2016 - day 1</a></h1><span class="publishing-info"><span class="date">29 de Fevereiro de 2016, 20:44</span><span class="author">, por <a href="http://softwarelivre.org/terceiro">Antonio Terceiro</a></span><span class="comments"> - <a href="/terceiro/blog/debian-ruby-sprint-2016-day-1#comments_list"><span class='comment-count hide'>0</span><span class='comment-count-write-out'>sem comentários ainda</span></a></span></span><p>This year&#8217;s <a href="https://wiki.debian.org/Teams/Ruby/Meeting/Brazil2016">Debian Ruby team sprint</a> started today here at Curitiba. Everyone arrived fine, and we started working at the meeting room we have booked for the week at Curitiba campus of the <a href="http://utfpr.edu.br/" title="UTPFR">Federal Technical University of Paraná</a>. The room is at the &#8220;Department of Business and Community Relations&#8221;, what makes a lot of sense! :-)</p>
